theorem
Th54: (a <> ( 0 ) implies ( a #Z ( k + l ) ) = ( ( a #Z k ) * ( a #Z l ) ))
proof
assume A1: a <> ( 0 );
per cases ;
suppose A2: (k >= ( 0 ) & l >= ( 0 ));

then A3: ( k * l ) >= ( 0 );
thus ( a #Z ( k + l ) ) = ( a |^ ( abs ( k + l ) ) ) by A2,CKB41:def 1
.= ( a |^ ( ( abs k ) + ( abs l ) ) ) by A3,ABSVALUE:11
.= ( ( a |^ ( abs k ) ) * ( a |^ ( abs l ) ) ) by NEWTON:8
.= ( ( a #Z k ) * ( a |^ ( abs l ) ) ) by A2,CKB41:def 1
.= ( ( a #Z k ) * ( a #Z l ) ) by A2,CKB41:def 1;
end;
suppose A4: (k >= ( 0 ) & l < ( 0 ));

then reconsider m = k as (Element of ( NAT )) by INT_1:3;
reconsider n = ( - l ) as (Element of ( NAT )) by A4,INT_1:3;
( k + l ) = ( m - n );
hence ( a #Z ( k + l ) ) = ( ( a |^ m ) / ( a |^ n ) ) by A1,CKB54:1
.= ( ( a |^ m ) * ( ( a |^ n ) " ) )
.= ( ( a |^ ( abs k ) ) * ( ( a |^ n ) " ) ) by ABSVALUE:def 1
.= ( ( a |^ ( abs k ) ) * ( ( a |^ ( abs ( - l ) ) ) " ) ) by ABSVALUE:def 1
.= ( ( a |^ ( abs k ) ) * ( ( a |^ ( abs l ) ) " ) ) by COMPLEX1:52
.= ( ( a #Z k ) * ( ( a |^ ( abs l ) ) " ) ) by A4,CKB41:def 1
.= ( ( a #Z k ) * ( a #Z l ) ) by A4,CKB41:def 1;
end;
suppose A5: (k < ( 0 ) & l >= ( 0 ));

